tep result\n  - `message`: the log content\n  - `timestamp`: when the log was written\n\n### 2. gRPC Protocol Definition\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 10, 70-86)\n\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);\n  ...\n}\n\nmessage StreamLogsRequest {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string log_type = 3;\n  bool follow = 4;      // passed via metadata x-cloche-follow\n  int32 limit = 5;      // passed via metadata x-cloche-limit\n}\n\nmessage LogEntry {\n  string type = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string result = 3;\n  string message = 4;\n  string timestamp = 5;\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Daemon-Side Log Streaming (gRPC Server)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 666-976)\n\nThe `StreamLogs` RPC implementation has a sophisticated multi-mode system:\n\n**Mode 1: Full Log for Completed Runs**\n- Reads `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log` (unified log file)\n- Sends as a single `full_log` entry\n- Returns `run_completed` entry with final state\n\n**Mode 2: Live Streaming for Active Runs**\n- Uses the `logBroadcast` broadcaster for real-time streaming\n- Subscribes to live log lines published by the agent/host executor\n- Automatically enters \"follow\" mode for active runs\n- Returns `log` entries as they arrive\n\n**Mode 3: Filtered Logs by Step/Type**\n- Uses `logStore` (SQLite index) if available\n- Falls back to file path conventions:\n  - `<step>.log` for full step output\n  - `llm-<step>.log` for LLM interaction logs\n- Supported types: `full`, `script`, `llm`\n- Returns `step_log` entries with filtered content\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `applyLimit()`: Returns last N lines of content\n- `followFromContext()`: Extracts follow flag from gRPC metadata\n- `limitFromContext()`: Extracts line limit from gRPC metadata\n\n### 4. Log Storage and Directory Structure\n\n**Output Directory Convention:**\n```\n.cloche/\n├── <run-id>/\n│   ├── output/\n│   │   ├── full.log              # Unified log (all steps, all types)\n│   │   ├── <step>.log            # Per-step log file (agent/script output)\n│   │   ├── <step>.out            # Host workflow step output\n│   │   ├── llm-<step>.log        # LLM interaction log (copy for agent steps)\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── prompt.txt                # Run-specific prompt (for agents)\n│   └── context.json              # Run context store (key-value pairs)\n├── history.log                   # Protocol history (step:result pairs)\n└── ...\n```\n\n### 5. Unified Log Writer\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` (lines 21-67)\n\nThe `Writer` type writes to `.cloche/output/full.log`:\n- Thread-safe (uses mutex)\n- Appends timestamped, type-prefixed entries\n- Format: `[timestamp] [type] message\\n`\n- Entry types: `status`, `script`, `llm`\n\n**Used by:**\n- Agent runner in container workflows\n- Host workflow runner\n- Captures step-level logs + status events\n\n### 6. Live Log Broadcasting\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` (lines 31-141)\n\nThe `Broadcaster` fans out log lines to multiple subscribers:\n- Maintains per-run broadcast channels\n- Non-blocking publish (drops lines if subscriber is slow)\n- Subscription returns a `Subscriber` with a channel of `LogLine` entries\n- Automatically closes channels when `Finish(runID)` is called\n\n**LogLine structure:**\n```go\ntype LogLine struct {\n    Timestamp string // RFC3339\n    Type      string // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    Content   string // the message\n    StepName  string // originating step\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Agent-Side Log Writing\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` (lines 71-214)\n\nContainer agent workflow execution:\n1. Creates unified log writer via `logstream.New(workDir)` → writes to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n2. For each step:\n   - Logs `step_started` status event\n   - Executes the step (script/agent)\n   - Logs step output by reading per-step `.log` files\n   - For agent steps: copies `<step>.log` to `llm-<step>.log`\n   - Logs `step_completed` status event\n3. Logs `run_completed` with final result\n\n**Per-step file writing:**\n- Script steps: adapter writes to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- Agent (prompt) steps: adapter writes to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- Agent logs are also copied to `llm-<step>.log`\n\n### 8. Host Workflow Log Writing\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` (lines 113-135)\n\nHost workflow execution:\n1. Creates unified log writer: `logstream.New(runDir)` → `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log`\n2. Sets up status handler for step events\n3. Executor writes step outputs to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.out` files\n4. Status handler logs step_started, step_completed, and run_completed events\n\n**Host executor output:**\n- Script steps: writes stdout+stderr to `<step>.out`\n- Workflow steps: writes child run ID to `<step>.out`\n- Agent steps: reads from adapter output, writes to `<step>.out`\n\n### 9. Log Stream Parsing\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` (lines 1-232)\n\nProcesses Claude Code stream-json output:\n- `ParseClaudeLine()`: Parses single JSON line, extracts human-readable text\n- `ParseClaudeStream()`: Processes multi-line stream, filters protocol events\n- Extracts assistant text, tool call summaries, result events\n- Skips system events, user interactions, and protocol-only events\n- Formats tool calls as: `ToolName('parameter')`\n\n### 10. Web UI Log Display\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1067-1278)\n\nTwo HTTP endpoints for logs:\n\n**`GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` — Server-Sent Events (SSE)**\n- For active runs: subscribes to broadcaster, streams live log lines\n- For completed runs: serves `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log` as SSE events\n- Sends metadata event when skipping lines due to tail limit\n- Supports pagination and scrollback\n\n**`GET /api/runs/{id}/logs` — JSON API**\n- Reads full.log for paginated access\n- Query params: `end` (upper bound), `limit` (lines to return)\n- Response: `{lines, total, start, end}`\n- Used for loading earlier log lines\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `readVisibleLogLines()`: Reads and parses full.log, filters LLM protocol events\n- `parseFullLogLine()`: Parses `[timestamp] [type] content` format\n- `parseLLMLogLine()`: Extracts human-readable text from LLM JSON entries\n- `streamFullLog()`: Streams archived log as SSE events\n\n### 11. Web UI Frontend\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 101-349)\n\nLog viewer on the run detail page:\n- Connects to SSE stream at `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Displays logs with color-coding by type (log-type-status, log-type-script, log-type-llm)\n- Auto-scrolls to bottom when at bottom of view\n- Shows \"Load earlier\" button when initial load is capped\n- Fetches earlier lines via `/api/runs/{id}/logs?end=N&limit=N` API\n- Updates step execution table in real-time for active runs\n\n### 12. LogStore Port and Index\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 27-42)\n\nLogStore interface for indexed log file lookups:\n```go\ntype LogFileEntry struct {\n    ID        int64\n    RunID     string\n    StepName  string\n    FileType  string // \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    FilePath  string\n    FileSize  int64\n    CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n(No SQLite implementation currently committed, but interface exists for future indexing)\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Data Flow\n\n1. **Agent/Executor writes** → per-step `.log` files + unified `full.log`\n2. **Broadcaster publishes** → real-time log lines to subscribers (for active runs)\n3. **gRPC StreamLogs** → reads full.log or subscribes to broadcaster\n4. **CLI/Web receives** → LogEntry messages via stream or HTTP\n5. **Web UI** → displays logs with real-time updates and scrollback\n\nThis architecture supports:\n- Live streaming for active runs\n- Full log retrieval for completed runs\n- Filtered logs by step/type\n- Pagination and scrollback\n- Multiple output formats (gRPC, HTTP/SSE, JSON API)"}],"totalDurationMs":79743,"totalTokens":95198,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1012,"cache_read_input_tokens":91377,"output_tokens":2809,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1012},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
