{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017DUhYuD7aYhBXvUGLfoFvW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package agent\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"fmt\"\n     6→\t\"io\"\n     7→\t\"os\"\n     8→\t\"path/filepath\"\n     9→\t\"strings\"\n    10→\n    11→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/generic\"\n    12→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/prompt\"\n    13→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    14→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    15→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/engine\"\n    16→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    18→)\n    19→\n    20→type RunnerConfig struct {\n    21→\tWorkflowPath   string\n    22→\tWorkDir        string\n    23→\tStatusOutput   io.Writer\n    24→\tRunID          string\n    25→\tResumeFromStep string // when non-empty, resume the workflow from this step\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→type Runner struct {\n    29→\tcfg RunnerConfig\n    30→}\n    31→\n    32→func NewRunner(cfg RunnerConfig) *Runner {\n    33→\treturn &Runner{\n    34→\t\tcfg: cfg,\n    35→\t}\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→func (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context) error {\n    39→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(r.cfg.WorkflowPath)\n    40→\tif err != nil {\n    41→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"reading workflow file: %w\", err)\n    42→\t}\n    43→\n    44→\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n    45→\tif err != nil {\n    46→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"parsing workflow: %w\", err)\n    47→\t}\n    48→\n    49→\tstatusWriter := protocol.NewStatusWriter(r.cfg.StatusOutput)\n    50→\tgenericAdapter := generic.New()\n    51→\tgenericAdapter.RunID = r.cfg.RunID\n    52→\tpromptAdapter := prompt.New()\n    53→\tpromptAdapter.RunID = r.cfg.RunID\n    54→\tpromptAdapter.StatusWriter = statusWriter\n    55→\tif cmd, ok := os.LookupEnv(\"CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND\"); ok {\n    56→\t\tpromptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n    57→\t}\n    58→\tif cmd := wf.Config[\"container.agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n    59→\t\tpromptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n    60→\t}\n    61→\tif args := wf.Config[\"container.agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n    62→\t\tpromptAdapter.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n    63→\t}\n    64→\n    65→\t// Reset per-run state from any previous run — but preserve outputs when resuming\n    66→\t_ = os.RemoveAll(filepath.Join(r.cfg.WorkDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\"))\n    67→\tif r.cfg.ResumeFromStep == \"\" {\n    68→\t\t_ = os.RemoveAll(filepath.Join(r.cfg.WorkDir, \".cloche\", \"output\"))\n    69→\t}\n    70→\n    71→\t// Create unified log writer\n    72→\tulog, err := logstream.New(r.cfg.WorkDir)\n    73→\tif err != nil {\n    74→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating unified log: %w\", err)\n    75→\t}\n    76→\tdefer ulog.Close()\n    77→\n    78→\tgenericAdapter.StatusWriter = statusWriter\n    79→\n    80→\texecutor := &stepExecutor{\n    81→\t\tworkDir:        r.cfg.WorkDir,\n    82→\t\tgeneric:        genericAdapter,\n    83→\t\tprompt:         promptAdapter,\n    84→\t\tlogStream:      ulog,\n    85→\t\tstatusWriter:   statusWriter,\n    86→\t\tresumeFromStep: r.cfg.ResumeFromStep,\n    87→\t}\n    88→\n    89→\teng := engine.New(executor)\n    90→\teng.SetStatusHandler(&statusReporter{writer: statusWriter, logStream: ulog})\n    91→\n    92→\t// Resume mode: load completed step results and configure engine\n    93→\tif r.cfg.ResumeFromStep != \"\" {\n    94→\t\tpreloaded, err := loadCompletedStepResults(r.cfg.WorkDir, wf, r.cfg.ResumeFromStep)\n    95→\t\tif err != nil {\n    96→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"loading completed step results for resume: %w\", err)\n    97→\t\t}\n    98→\t\teng.SetPreloadedResults(preloaded)\n    99→\t}\n   100→\n   101→\t// Generate a run title from the prompt if one was not provided by the caller.\n   102→\t// The daemon sets title from --title; if empty, the agent extracts from prompt.\n   103→\tif title := extractTitle(r.cfg.WorkDir, r.cfg.RunID); title != \"\" {\n   104→\t\tstatusWriter.RunTitle(title)\n   105→\t}\n   106→\n   107→\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:start \"+wf.Name)\n   108→\n   109→\trun, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n   110→\tif runErr != nil {\n   111→\t\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:end \"+wf.Name+\" result:failed\")\n   112→\t\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"error: \"+runErr.Error())\n   113→\t\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"run_completed: failed\")\n   114→\t\t// Extract the failed step name from step executions so the daemon\n   115→\t\t// can display which step caused the failure.\n   116→\t\tfailedStep := \"\"\n   117→\t\tif run != nil {\n   118→\t\t\tfor _, se := range run.StepExecutions {\n   119→\t\t\t\tif se.Result == \"error\" || se.Result == \"fail\" {\n   120→\t\t\t\t\tfailedStep = se.StepName\n   121→\t\t\t\t}\n   122→\t\t\t}\n   123→\t\t}\n   124→\t\tstatusWriter.Error(failedStep, runErr.Error())\n   125→\t\tstatusWriter.RunCompleted(\"failed\")\n   126→\t\treturn runErr\n   127→\t}\n   128→\n   129→\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:end \"+wf.Name+\" result:\"+string(run.State))\n   130→\n   131→\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"run_completed: \"+string(run.State))\n   132→\tstatusWriter.RunCompleted(string(run.State))\n   133→\treturn nil\n   134→}\n   135→\n   136→type stepExecutor struct {\n   137→\tworkDir        string\n   138→\tgeneric        *generic.Adapter\n   139→\tprompt         *prompt.Adapter\n   140→\tlogStream      *logstream.Writer\n   141→\tstatusWriter   *protocol.StatusWriter\n   142→\tresumeFromStep string // the step being resumed (for prompt resume mode)\n   143→}\n   144→\n   145→func (e *stepExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n   146→\tswitch step.Type {\n   147→\tcase domain.StepTypeScript:\n   148→\t\tresult, err := e.generic.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n   149→\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeScript)\n   150→\t\treturn result, err\n   151→\tcase domain.StepTypeAgent:\n   152→\t\tif _, ok := step.Config[\"run\"]; ok {\n   153→\t\t\tresult, err := e.generic.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n   154→\t\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeScript)\n   155→\t\t\treturn result, err\n   156→\t\t}\n   157→\t\tif _, ok := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; ok {\n   158→\t\t\tif cmd := step.Config[\"agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n   159→\t\t\t\te.prompt.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n   160→\t\t\t}\n   161→\t\t\tif args := step.Config[\"agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n   162→\t\t\t\te.prompt.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n   163→\t\t\t}\n   164→\t\t\t// Resume mode: if this is the step being resumed, use conversation resume\n   165→\t\t\tif e.resumeFromStep == step.Name {\n   166→\t\t\t\te.prompt.ResumeConversation = true\n   167→\t\t\t\tdefer func() { e.prompt.ResumeConversation = false }()\n   168→\t\t\t}\n   169→\t\t\tresult, err := e.prompt.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n   170→\t\t\te.copyToLLMLog(step.Name)\n   171→\t\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeLLM)\n   172→\t\t\treturn result, err\n   173→\t\t}\n   174→\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"agent step %q requires either 'run' or 'prompt' config\", step.Name)\n   175→\tdefault:\n   176→\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"unknown step type: %s\", step.Type)\n   177→\t}\n   178→}\n   179→\n   180→// logStepOutput reads the per-step log file and writes its contents to the unified log.\n   181→func (e *stepExecutor) logStepOutput(stepName string, typ logstream.EntryType) {\n   182→\tpath := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", stepName+\".log\")\n   183→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n   184→\tif err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\n   185→\t\treturn\n   186→\t}\n   187→\te.logStream.Log(typ, string(data))\n   188→}\n   189→\n   190→// copyToLLMLog copies <step>.log to llm-<step>.log for agent prompt steps.\n   191→func (e *stepExecutor) copyToLLMLog(stepName string) {\n   192→\tsrc := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", stepName+\".log\")\n   193→\tdst := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", \"llm-\"+stepName+\".log\")\n   194→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(src)\n   195→\tif err != nil {\n   196→\t\treturn\n   197→\t}\n   198→\t_ = os.WriteFile(dst, data, 0644)\n   199→}\n   200→\n   201→type statusReporter struct {\n   202→\twriter    *protocol.StatusWriter\n   203→\tlogStream *logstream.Writer\n   204→}\n   205→\n   206→func (s *statusReporter) OnStepStart(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step) {\n   207→\ts.writer.StepStarted(step.Name)\n   208→\ts.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"step_started: \"+step.Name)\n   209→}\n   210→\n   211→func (s *statusReporter) OnStepComplete(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string) {\n   212→\ts.writer.StepCompleted(step.Name, result)\n   213→\ts.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"step_completed: \"+step.Name+\" -> \"+result)\n   214→}\n   215→\n   216→func (s *statusReporter) OnRunComplete(_ *domain.Run) {}\n   217→\n   218→// loadCompletedStepResults builds a map of step_name -> result for all steps\n   219→// that completed successfully before the resume point. It walks the workflow\n   220→// graph from the entry step, following wires, collecting results from the\n   221→// history log. Steps at or after the resumeFrom step are excluded.\n   222→func loadCompletedStepResults(workDir string, wf *domain.Workflow, resumeFrom string) (map[string]string, error) {\n   223→\tpreloaded := make(map[string]string)\n   224→\n   225→\t// Parse step results from history.log\n   226→\thistoryPath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"history.log\")\n   227→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(historyPath)\n   228→\tif err != nil {\n   229→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading history log: %w\", err)\n   230→\t}\n   231→\n   232→\t// Extract step:result pairs from history entries\n   233→\tstepResults := make(map[string]string)\n   234→\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n   235→\t\t// History format: [timestamp] step:<name> result:<result> ...\n   236→\t\tif !strings.Contains(line, \"step:\") || !strings.Contains(line, \"result:\") {\n   237→\t\t\tcontinue\n   238→\t\t}\n   239→\t\tvar stepName, result string\n   240→\t\tfor _, field := range strings.Fields(line) {\n   241→\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(field, \"step:\") {\n   242→\t\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(field, \"step:\")\n   243→\t\t\t}\n   244→\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(field, \"result:\") {\n   245→\t\t\t\tresult = strings.TrimPrefix(field, \"result:\")\n   246→\t\t\t}\n   247→\t\t}\n   248→\t\tif stepName != \"\" && result != \"\" {\n   249→\t\t\tstepResults[stepName] = result\n   250→\t\t}\n   251→\t}\n   252→\n   253→\t// Walk the workflow graph from entry step, collecting completed steps\n   254→\t// until we reach the resume step\n   255→\tvisited := make(map[string]bool)\n   256→\tvar walk func(stepName string)\n   257→\twalk = func(stepName string) {\n   258→\t\tif visited[stepName] || stepName == resumeFrom {\n   259→\t\t\treturn\n   260→\t\t}\n   261→\t\tvisited[stepName] = true\n   262→\n   263→\t\tresult, ok := stepResults[stepName]\n   264→\t\tif !ok {\n   265→\t\t\treturn\n   266→\t\t}\n   267→\t\tpreloaded[stepName] = result\n   268→\n   269→\t\t// Follow wires from this step's result\n   270→\t\tnextSteps, err := wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)\n   271→\t\tif err != nil {\n   272→\t\t\treturn\n   273→\t\t}\n   274→\t\tfor _, next := range nextSteps {\n   275→\t\t\tif next != domain.StepDone && next != domain.StepAbort {\n   276→\t\t\t\twalk(next)\n   277→\t\t\t}\n   278→\t\t}\n   279→\t}\n   280→\n   281→\twalk(wf.EntryStep)\n   282→\treturn preloaded, nil\n   283→}\n   284→\n   285→// extractTitle tries to derive a one-line summary from the run's prompt content.\n   286→// It reads the per-run prompt.txt file (written by the daemon before container start),\n   287→// then returns the first non-empty line, truncated to 100 characters.\n   288→func extractTitle(workDir string, runID string) string {\n   289→\t// Try the per-run prompt file\n   290→\tpromptPath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"prompt.txt\")\n   291→\tif _, err := os.Stat(promptPath); err != nil {\n   292→\t\t// Fall back to legacy path\n   293→\t\tpromptPath = filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"prompt.txt\")\n   294→\t}\n   295→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(promptPath)\n   296→\tif err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\n   297→\t\treturn \"\"\n   298→\t}\n   299→\n   300→\ttext := strings.TrimSpace(string(data))\n   301→\tif text == \"\" {\n   302→\t\treturn \"\"\n   303→\t}\n   304→\n   305→\t// Take first non-empty line as the title\n   306→\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(text, \"\\n\") {\n   307→\t\tline = strings.TrimSpace(line)\n   308→\t\t// Skip markdown headers, comment markers, and blank lines\n   309→\t\tif line == \"\" || line == \"---\" || line == \"```\" {\n   310→\t\t\tcontinue\n   311→\t\t}\n   312→\t\t// Strip leading markdown header markers\n   313→\t\tline = strings.TrimLeft(line, \"# \")\n   314→\t\tline = strings.TrimSpace(line)\n   315→\t\tif line == \"\" {\n   316→\t\t\tcontinue\n   317→\t\t}\n   318→\t\tif len(line) > 100 {\n   319→\t\t\tline = line[:97] + \"...\"\n   320→\t\t}\n   321→\t\treturn line\n   322→\t}\n   323→\treturn \"\"\n   324→}\n   325→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"a6f58286-45a8-445c-ba88-3b2adf895a22","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go","content":"package agent\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/generic\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/prompt\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/engine\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n)\n\ntype RunnerConfig struct {\n\tWorkflowPath   string\n\tWorkDir        string\n\tStatusOutput   io.Writer\n\tRunID          string\n\tResumeFromStep string // when non-empty, resume the workflow from this step\n}\n\ntype Runner struct {\n\tcfg RunnerConfig\n}\n\nfunc NewRunner(cfg RunnerConfig) *Runner {\n\treturn &Runner{\n\t\tcfg: cfg,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context) error {\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(r.cfg.WorkflowPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"reading workflow file: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"parsing workflow: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tstatusWriter := protocol.NewStatusWriter(r.cfg.StatusOutput)\n\tgenericAdapter := generic.New()\n\tgenericAdapter.RunID = r.cfg.RunID\n\tpromptAdapter := prompt.New()\n\tpromptAdapter.RunID = r.cfg.RunID\n\tpromptAdapter.StatusWriter = statusWriter\n\tif cmd, ok := os.LookupEnv(\"CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND\"); ok {\n\t\tpromptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n\t}\n\tif cmd := wf.Config[\"container.agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\tpromptAdapter.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n\t}\n\tif args := wf.Config[\"container.agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n\t\tpromptAdapter.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n\t}\n\n\t// Reset per-run state from any previous run — but preserve outputs when resuming\n\t_ = os.RemoveAll(filepath.Join(r.cfg.WorkDir, \".cloche\", \"attempt_count\"))\n\tif r.cfg.ResumeFromStep == \"\" {\n\t\t_ = os.RemoveAll(filepath.Join(r.cfg.WorkDir, \".cloche\", \"output\"))\n\t}\n\n\t// Create unified log writer\n\tulog, err := logstream.New(r.cfg.WorkDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating unified log: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tdefer ulog.Close()\n\n\tgenericAdapter.StatusWriter = statusWriter\n\n\texecutor := &stepExecutor{\n\t\tworkDir:        r.cfg.WorkDir,\n\t\tgeneric:        genericAdapter,\n\t\tprompt:         promptAdapter,\n\t\tlogStream:      ulog,\n\t\tstatusWriter:   statusWriter,\n\t\tresumeFromStep: r.cfg.ResumeFromStep,\n\t}\n\n\teng := engine.New(executor)\n\teng.SetStatusHandler(&statusReporter{writer: statusWriter, logStream: ulog})\n\n\t// Resume mode: load completed step results and configure engine\n\tif r.cfg.ResumeFromStep != \"\" {\n\t\tpreloaded, err := loadCompletedStepResults(r.cfg.WorkDir, wf, r.cfg.ResumeFromStep)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"loading completed step results for resume: %w\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t\teng.SetPreloadedResults(preloaded)\n\t}\n\n\t// Generate a run title from the prompt if one was not provided by the caller.\n\t// The daemon sets title from --title; if empty, the agent extracts from prompt.\n\tif title := extractTitle(r.cfg.WorkDir, r.cfg.RunID); title != \"\" {\n\t\tstatusWriter.RunTitle(title)\n\t}\n\n\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:start \"+wf.Name)\n\n\trun, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n\tif runErr != nil {\n\t\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:end \"+wf.Name+\" result:failed\")\n\t\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"error: \"+runErr.Error())\n\t\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"run_completed: failed\")\n\t\t// Extract the failed step name from step executions so the daemon\n\t\t// can display which step caused the failure.\n\t\tfailedStep := \"\"\n\t\tif run != nil {\n\t\t\tfor _, se := range run.StepExecutions {\n\t\t\t\tif se.Result == \"error\" || se.Result == \"fail\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tfailedStep = se.StepName\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tstatusWriter.Error(failedStep, runErr.Error())\n\t\tstatusWriter.RunCompleted(\"failed\")\n\t\treturn runErr\n\t}\n\n\tprotocol.AppendHistoryMarker(r.cfg.WorkDir, \"workflow:end \"+wf.Name+\" result:\"+string(run.State))\n\n\tulog.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"run_completed: \"+string(run.State))\n\tstatusWriter.RunCompleted(string(run.State))\n\treturn nil\n}\n\ntype stepExecutor struct {\n\tworkDir        string\n\tgeneric        *generic.Adapter\n\tprompt         *prompt.Adapter\n\tlogStream      *logstream.Writer\n\tstatusWriter   *protocol.StatusWriter\n\tresumeFromStep string // the step being resumed (for prompt resume mode)\n}\n\nfunc (e *stepExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error) {\n\tswitch step.Type {\n\tcase domain.StepTypeScript:\n\t\tresult, err := e.generic.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeScript)\n\t\treturn result, err\n\tcase domain.StepTypeAgent:\n\t\tif _, ok := step.Config[\"run\"]; ok {\n\t\t\tresult, err := e.generic.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n\t\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeScript)\n\t\t\treturn result, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif _, ok := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; ok {\n\t\t\tif cmd := step.Config[\"agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\te.prompt.Commands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif args := step.Config[\"agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\te.prompt.ExplicitArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t// Resume mode: if this is the step being resumed, use conversation resume\n\t\t\tif e.resumeFromStep == step.Name {\n\t\t\t\te.prompt.ResumeConversation = true\n\t\t\t\tdefer func() { e.prompt.ResumeConversation = false }()\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tresult, err := e.prompt.Execute(ctx, step, e.workDir)\n\t\t\te.copyToLLMLog(step.Name)\n\t\t\te.logStepOutput(step.Name, logstream.TypeLLM)\n\t\t\treturn result, err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"agent step %q requires either 'run' or 'prompt' config\", step.Name)\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"unknown step type: %s\", step.Type)\n\t}\n}\n\n// logStepOutput reads the per-step log file and writes its contents to the unified log.\nfunc (e *stepExecutor) logStepOutput(stepName string, typ logstream.EntryType) {\n\tpath := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", stepName+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n\tif err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\te.logStream.Log(typ, string(data))\n}\n\n// copyToLLMLog copies <step>.log to llm-<step>.log for agent prompt steps.\nfunc (e *stepExecutor) copyToLLMLog(stepName string) {\n\tsrc := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", stepName+\".log\")\n\tdst := filepath.Join(e.workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\", \"llm-\"+stepName+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(src)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\t_ = os.WriteFile(dst, data, 0644)\n}\n\ntype statusReporter struct {\n\twriter    *protocol.StatusWriter\n\tlogStream *logstream.Writer\n}\n\nfunc (s *statusReporter) OnStepStart(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step) {\n\ts.writer.StepStarted(step.Name)\n\ts.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"step_started: \"+step.Name)\n}\n\nfunc (s *statusReporter) OnStepComplete(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string) {\n\ts.writer.StepCompleted(step.Name, result)\n\ts.logStream.Log(logstream.TypeStatus, \"step_completed: \"+step.Name+\" -> \"+result)\n}\n\nfunc (s *statusReporter) OnRunComplete(_ *domain.Run) {}\n\n// loadCompletedStepResults builds a map of step_name -> result for all steps\n// that completed successfully before the resume point. It walks the workflow\n// graph from the entry step, following wires, collecting results from the\n// history log. Steps at or after the resumeFrom step are excluded.\nfunc loadCompletedStepResults(workDir string, wf *domain.Workflow, resumeFrom string) (map[string]string, error) {\n\tpreloaded := make(map[string]string)\n\n\t// Parse step results from history.log\n\thistoryPath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"history.log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(historyPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading history log: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Extract step:result pairs from history entries\n\tstepResults := make(map[string]string)\n\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n\t\t// History format: [timestamp] step:<name> result:<result> ...\n\t\tif !strings.Contains(line, \"step:\") || !strings.Contains(line, \"result:\") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar stepName, result string\n\t\tfor _, field := range strings.Fields(line) {\n\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(field, \"step:\") {\n\t\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(field, \"step:\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(field, \"result:\") {\n\t\t\t\tresult = strings.TrimPrefix(field, \"result:\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tif stepName != \"\" && result != \"\" {\n\t\t\tstepResults[stepName] = result\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Walk the workflow graph from entry step, collecting completed steps\n\t// until we reach the resume step\n\tvisited := make(map[string]bool)\n\tvar walk func(stepName string)\n\twalk = func(stepName string) {\n\t\tif visited[stepName] || stepName == resumeFrom {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\tvisited[stepName] = true\n\n\t\tresult, ok := stepResults[stepName]\n\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\tpreloaded[stepName] = result\n\n\t\t// Follow wires from this step's result\n\t\tnextSteps, err := wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t\tfor _, next := range nextSteps {\n\t\t\tif next != domain.StepDone && next != domain.StepAbort {\n\t\t\t\twalk(next)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\twalk(wf.EntryStep)\n\treturn preloaded, nil\n}\n\n// extractTitle tries to derive a one-line summary from the run's prompt content.\n// It reads the per-run prompt.txt file (written by the daemon before container start),\n// then returns the first non-empty line, truncated to 100 characters.\nfunc extractTitle(workDir string, runID string) string {\n\t// Try the per-run prompt file\n\tpromptPath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"prompt.txt\")\n\tif _, err := os.Stat(promptPath); err != nil {\n\t\t// Fall back to legacy path\n\t\tpromptPath = filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"prompt.txt\")\n\t}\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(promptPath)\n\tif err != nil || len(data) == 0 {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\n\ttext := strings.TrimSpace(string(data))\n\tif text == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\n\t// Take first non-empty line as the title\n\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(text, \"\\n\") {\n\t\tline = strings.TrimSpace(line)\n\t\t// Skip markdown headers, comment markers, and blank lines\n\t\tif line == \"\" || line == \"---\" || line == \"```\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Strip leading markdown header markers\n\t\tline = strings.TrimLeft(line, \"# \")\n\t\tline = strings.TrimSpace(line)\n\t\tif line == \"\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif len(line) > 100 {\n\t\t\tline = line[:97] + \"...\"\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn line\n\t}\n\treturn \"\"\n}\n","numLines":325,"startLine":1,"totalLines":325}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018BSi8HTHqPrhzKMHqci4Qx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the problem. Let me trace through the issues:\n\n1. **`cloche logs <run id> -s <step>` is broken**: The `streamFilteredLogs` method (line 872) looks for `<step>.log` files in the output directory. For host workflows, the executor writes `<step>.out` files, not `<step>.log` files. The fallback path convention only checks `.log` (line 923), not `.out`.\n\n2. **Per-step `.log` files are missing for host runs**: The host `Executor` writes output to `<step>.out` but doesn't create `<step>.log` files. \n\n3. **`hostStatusHandler.OnStepComplete` reads from `<step>.out` for broadcasting but never writes the corresponding `.log` file**.\n\nSo the fixes needed are:\n\n1. **Host executor**: After step completion, write `<step>.log` file from the step output (copy `.out` to `.log` or write directly as `.log`).\n\n2. **`streamFilteredLogs`**: Also check `.out` extension as a fallback when `.log` is not found.\n\n3. **Web UI**: Need to verify if the web UI properly streams per-step logs.\n\nNow I need to examine how the host executor writes output files and trace through the web handler's streaming logic.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9001,"cache_read_input_tokens":29075,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9001},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"b815e258-b700-45b8-8f41-33752bdc3ada"}
