{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Uc4iSVMSV5pfpQZfzaZv5","type":"tool_result","content":"   860→\n   861→\t// Try per-step output file\n   862→\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n   863→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n   864→\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   865→\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   866→\t\treturn\n   867→\t}\n   868→\n   869→\t// Do NOT fall back to container.log or live docker logs here — those\n   870→\t// contain unfiltered output from ALL steps and would show the wrong\n   871→\t// content for this specific step (the root cause of web-UI log mismatches).\n   872→\n   873→\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   874→}\n   875→\n   876→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStopRun(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   877→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   878→\n   879→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   880→\tif err != nil {\n   881→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   882→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   883→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n   884→\t\treturn\n   885→\t}\n   886→\n   887→\t// Only allow stopping active runs\n   888→\tif run.State != domain.RunStatePending && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning {\n   889→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   890→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   891→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run is not active\"})\n   892→\t\treturn\n   893→\t}\n   894→\n   895→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   896→\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   897→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   898→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   899→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"83a04633-00fb-4a86-b0ec-53ebfd19016f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go","content":"\n\t// Try per-step output file\n\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Do NOT fall back to container.log or live docker logs here — those\n\t// contain unfiltered output from ALL steps and would show the wrong\n\t// content for this specific step (the root cause of web-UI log mismatches).\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStopRun(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Only allow stopping active runs\n\tif run.State != domain.RunStatePending && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run is not active\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})","numLines":40,"startLine":860,"totalLines":1986}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HzukW29VKtBRsyNrq4fZT6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize the issues and fixes needed:\n\n## Issues\n\n1. **Per-step `.log` files missing for host workflows**: The host executor writes `<step>.out` files, but `streamFilteredLogs` (gRPC) and `handleAPIStepOutput` (web) look for `<step>.log`. The host `hostStatusHandler.OnStepComplete` doesn't write `.log` files.\n\n2. **`streamFilteredLogs` doesn't fall back to `.out`**: When `<step>.log` doesn't exist, it returns an error instead of trying `.out`.\n\n\n3. **`handleAPIStepOutput` has the same fallback issue**: The web UI step output handler also fails when `.log` files are missing instead of checking for `.out`.\n4. **Web UI lacks real-time per-step log streaming**: Currently the web UI shows a unified log stream, and step sections only fetch completed output on click rather than streaming updates as they happen.\n\n## Fixes\n\n### Fix 1: Write `<step>.log` files for host workflows\nIn `hostStatusHandler.OnStepComplete`, after reading the `.out` file, write a `.log` file copy.\n\n### Fix 2: Add fallback logic to both log handlers\nBoth `streamFilteredLogs` and `handleAPIStepOutput` need to attempt reading `.out` files when `.log` files don't exist.\n\n### Fix 3: Implement per-step streaming in the web UI\nThe broadcaster already includes step names, so I can add a step-specific SSE endpoint and update the step accordion to stream logs in real-time during active runs instead of doing a one-shot fetch when clicked.\n\nThe core problems boil down to two things: host runs aren't writing `.log` files so `cloche logs -s <step>` breaks, and the web UI step sections don't stream updates. Let me focus on implementing these fixes.\n\nFor the backend, I need to write `.log` files in `hostStatusHandler.OnStepComplete`, add fallback logic to `.out` files in both `streamFilteredLogs` and `handleAPIStepOutput`. For the frontend, when a step accordion opens during an active run, it should subscribe to a streaming endpoint that filters logs by step name rather than waiting for the run to complete. to SSE and filter by step name. Or I could add a step-specific SSE endpoint instead.\n\nLooking at the broadcaster, it already sends step_name, so the web UI can filter the main SSE stream by step name for per-step display. The most efficient approach is to maintain per-step buffers from the main stream—when a step accordion opens, I'll show the buffered content plus live updates.\n\nThe requirements call for logs to automatically appear in per-step sections as they stream in. I'll keep the unified log view at the bottom while making step accordions display their own logs, with both receiving updates during active runs. Let me start implementing the backend fixes first, then enhance the web UI.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":693,"cache_read_input_tokens":56126,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":693},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"10ced295-ed68-424b-bc9e-fa92173ac871"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HzukW29VKtBRsyNrq4fZT6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. The issues are:\n\n1. **Host workflows write `<step>.out` but not `<step>.log`** — so `cloche logs -s <step>` fails\n2. **`streamFilteredLogs` (gRPC) doesn't fall back to `.out`** when `.log` is missing\n3. **`handleAPIStepOutput` (web) doesn't fall back to `.out`** either\n4. **Web UI step accordions don't stream live logs** — only fetch on click for completed steps\n\nLet me implement the fixes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":693,"cache_read_input_tokens":56126,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":693},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"e6b4f024-29aa-4948-a3bf-f78a2affdb43"}
