{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011NXRSSxKfu4URXhf2uz2tS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of what was changed:\n\n**Root cause**: Host workflows wrote step output to `<step>.out` files, but the log system (`cloche logs -s`, web UI) expected `<step>.log` files.\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`internal/host/runner.go`** — `hostStatusHandler.OnStepComplete` now writes a `.log` copy of the `.out` file after step completion, so `cloche logs -s <step>` and the web UI can find per-step log output.\n\n2. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — `streamFilteredLogs` now tries `.out` as a fallback when `.log` doesn't exist (backward compat with older host runs).\n\n3. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** — `handleAPIStepOutput` now tries `.out` as a fallback when `.log` doesn't exist.\n\n4. **`internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`** — Step accordion sections now receive live-streamed log lines from the SSE stream, filtered by `step_name`. Lines are buffered per-step and auto-scroll is preserved (scrolls to bottom unless user scrolled up).\n\n5. **`internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** — Added `.step-log-viewer` wrapper for scrollable per-step log containers.\n\n6. **Tests added**: `TestHostStatusHandler_WritesStepLogFile`, `TestHostStatusHandler_NoLogFileWhenNoOutput`, `TestServer_StreamLogs_StepFilterFallbackToOut`, `TestStepOutput_FallsBackToOutFile`, `TestStepOutput_PrefersLogOverOut`.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":87657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":310},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab06b6b4-e6b6-4d23-a886-0560ffd72710","uuid":"008deb5b-e07d-4502-bbfa-99f62627715e"}
